@tomato-cc Cool, updated to the list

@jacksparrow414  hi,The routing result is correct,  Because you also configure sharding,
ou want to get all the users ,  you also config sharding table with t_user,
so,the result is salve_0.t_user_0, slave_1_t_user_1。

@hongfuli  As an alternative choice, we suggest:
- Plan A: You can remove all prefix of column: SELECT `user_id`, `order_id`, `name` FROM `t_order` ORDER BY `order_id` ASC  ;
- Plan B: You also can add an alias for  table: SELECT `t_order`.`user_id`, `t_order`.`order_id`, `t_order`.`name` FROM `t_order` as `t_order`  ORDER BY `t_order`.`order_id` ASC  ;
